  • Method Details

    • getBottomHoleTemperature

      public Integer getBottomHoleTemperature()
      Return bottom hole temperature for the wellbore.

      Sodir description:
      This is the estimated temperature at final total depth of the wellbore.

      int, corresponds to the Sodir property wlbBottomHoleTemperature.

      Returns:
      Bottom hole temperature in degrees Celsius. Null if N/A or unknown.

    • getSeismicLocation

      public String getSeismicLocation()
      Return seismic location.

      Sodir description:

      varchar(200), corresponds to the Sodir property wlbSeismicLocation.

      Returns:
      Seismic location. Null if N/A or unknown.

      Returns:
      Max inclination in degrees. Null if N/A or unknown.

    • getAgeAtTd

      public String getAgeAtTd()
      Return age of this wellbore.

      Sodir description:
      Age (according to Geologic Time Scale 2004 by F. M. Gradstein, et al. (2004)) of the oldest penetrated formation. May differ from age at TD for example in deviated wellbores.

      Examples of legal values:

      • CRETACEOUS
      • EARLY CRETACEOUS
      • LATE JURASSIC
      • EARLY PERMIAN
      • EARLY TRIASSIC
      • EOCENE

      varchar(40), corresponds to the Sodir property wlbAgeAtTd.

      Returns:
      Age of this wellbore. Null if N/A or unknown.

    • getFormationAtTd

      public String getFormationAtTd()
      Return formation of this wellbore.

      Sodir description:
      Name of the oldest lithostratigraphic unit penetrated by the wellbore. In most wellbores this is formation or group at total depth. May differ from formation or group at TD for example in wellbores drilled with high deviation or through faults.

      Examples of legal values:

      • AMUNDSEN FM
      • BALDER FM
      • BASEMENT
      • BLODÃ˜KS FM
      • BRYNE FM
      • BURTON FM
      • COOK FM
      • DRAKE FM
      • DRAUPNE FM
      • EKOFISK FM
      • DUNLIN GP

      varchar(40), corresponds to the Sodir property wlbFormationAtTd.

      Returns:
      Formation of this wellbore. Null if N/A or unknown.

    • getReentryExplorationActivity

      public String getReentryExplorationActivity()
      Return reason for reentry of this wellbore.

      Sodir description:
      Reason for reentry of the wellbore. Only relevant for exploration wellbores.

      Example of legal values:

      • DRILLING
      • DRILLING/PLUGGING
      • LOGGING
      • PLUGGING
      • TESTING
      • TESTING/PLUGGING

      varchar(40), corresponds to the Sodir property wlbReentryExplorationActivity.

      Returns:
      Reason for reentry of this wellbore. Null if N/A or unknown.

    • isReentry

      public Boolean isReentry()
      Check if this wellbore has been re-entered.

      Sodir description:
      Status whether the wellbore has been re-entered. When counting number of wellbores on the Norwegian continental shelf, only those not reentered are counted.

      varchar(3), corresponds to the Sodir property wlbReentry.
